div2.entryFree:

      ضَبِيبٌ The point, or edge, (syn. حَدّ, [in an. ex.
in the O, the former is meant by it,]) of a sword;
(O, K;) and so ↓ ضَبَّةٌ. (El-Khattábee, TA.)


      المُضَرِّسُ The lion, that chews the flesh of his
prey without swallowing it: (O, K:) or the lion;
so called because he does thus. (TA.)
